  • Type Parameters:
    N - 

    public class ContDistCustom
extends ContDist
    Distribution returning values according to a user-specified distribution function. It is important that the used function is an actual distribution function, meaning it must be strictly monotonically increasing from 0 to 1. You also need to specify the lower and upper bounds of the distribution, meaning the values at which the cumulative probability is 0 and 1 respectively. If these requirements are not fulfilled, the class might return false and/or no samples.
